<br>
Warrior<br>
Cleric<br>
Enchanter<br>
Wizard<br>
Druid<br>
Shaman<br>
<br>
Tanking, healing and buffing, crowd control and haste, DD damage, sowing and buffing, and slowing and buffing.<br>
<br>
However, the most EFFICIENT groups I've had differ wildly...Such as.<br>
<br>
Monk<br>
Monk<br>
Mage<br>
Beastlord<br>
Shaman<br>
Necro<br>
<br>
3 pets classes for tanking, beastlord for buffing and slowing and the pets, monks heal themselves with insane BW skills, and shaman dishes in required heals.<br>
<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
<br>
Mage<br>
Mage<br>
Mage<br>
Mage<br>
Monk<br>
Shaman<br>
<br>
It ended up being an AoE group, with monk pulling, and shaman healing monk. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=qaedainmagikot>Qaedain Magikot</A> at: 3/28/02 12:52:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzacatac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 688<br> <font color=#333333>(3/28/02 1:16:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What is the definition of  the &quot;Classic Group?&quot</span><hr size=1> Think I agree with zephyr the most.<br>
