<br>
As for the classics this grouping is especially true at lower levels, where everyone doesn't have a right-click item. <br>
<br>
Puller (Ranger)<br>
Tank (Warrior)<br>
Healer (Cleric)<br>
Crowd Control/Mana Buffs (Chanter)<br>
SoW Capable Buffer (Druid / Shammy)<br>
xTra dmg dealer (Wiz, Mage, Rogue, Necro)<br>
<br>
xTra dmg dealer was by design supposed to be one of the original nuking classes, but at higher levels, rogues become very efficient in that role. 2 nuking classes can replace one buffing class due to the extra damage provided.<br>
<br>
Enchanters and Clerics are probably the most sought after classes in the game to round out a group and I've never really seen a group turn down an extra warrior if they have a slot available too.<br>
