In dungeon hunting<br>
- You want to be able to deal with adds<br>
- You don't want runners to go far<br>
- You need a tank<br>
- You need some kind of heal<br>
- You need to deal damage<br>
- You need to pull<br>
<br>
So you could have<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> TANK</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> : War (pal/sk)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> HEALER</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  : Cleric (druid,shaman)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> CROWD CONTROLER</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  : Ench (bard)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> DAMAGE DEALER</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> : rogue (monk/sk/warior/wizard/mage)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> SNARER</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  : ranger (druid/sk/wizard)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Any other class</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NOTES</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> : <br>
<br>
- I wrote first the most classic thus most adapted class then under parenthesis the degraded versions that you would choose.<br>
- Sometimes the degraded versions come really short before the other ones. For instance, Warrior/SK is a hard choice, if you choose the SK, you will have the possibility to have a main tank/puller/snarer all in one, then you free some places for other damage dealers preferably rogues if there are some available.<br>
- I don't list pullers because any class can pull. The best puller ever that I know 2 clerics, 1 shaman, an ench that can pull wonders, far better than most monk/sk that I know.<br>
- I don't want you to think that this is the kind of group I like to do, I just tried to make a good description of the classic group.<br>
<br>
My personnal feeling is you can build a lot of really strong groups around shamans.<br>
<br>
Now I will try to talk about what you would need to make a good group.<br>
Hunting humanoids :<br>
- A shamy<br>
- Possibly a tank if the mobs hit really hard<br>
- As many rogues as you can(at least 2 rogues)<br>
- If you don't have at least 3 rogues add a wizard/mage <br>
Mobs dying in less than 5 seconds don't need crowd control, don't require much heal. Shamy will slow, buff and occasionnaly heal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kryskin>Kryskin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(3/28/02 12:00:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  The &quot;Classic group&quot;</span><hr size=1> 1) Me.<br>
