<br>
Rangers have some serious HP and AC issues before level 50.  After 50 they are a great addition to any group.  Lots of damage, lots of utility spells.<br>
<br>
<br>
My favorite group currently is:<br>
<br>
<br>
Shaman<br>
Shaman<br>
Bard<br>
Monk<br>
Druid<br>
Other<br>
<br>
<br>
As a bard, I can keep any shaman in mana forever, and take them from OOM to full in about a minute and a half.  Monks just flat own warriors for XP grinding.  They generally have better AC, to a huge amount of damage, and can control the pace of pulls much better.  Druids offer the group SoW, snare, nukes and backup healing, while two FOM shamans can buff, debuff, slow, etc.<br>
<br>
The last slot would preferably be a dmage class, I.E. wizzie, mage, rogue, whatever.  As long as the player knows their class and doesn't whine incessantly, I'm willing to work with anyone.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 523<br> <font color=#333333>(3/28/02 3:40:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=21>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is the definition of  the &quot;Classic Group?&quot</span><hr size=1> I thought &quot;classic group&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> was</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> intended to be the &quot;most effective&quot;.<br>
<br>
Since this is a mage forum, I'm sure the question was intended to ask where the magician fits into a classic group.<br>
<br>
Frankly, they don't.  Neither do shadowknights, paladins or necros.  Even for AE groups, wizards are far superior, having 2 good post-50 spells they can chaincast for a lot higher DPS than a mage.<br>
<br>
Mages, like SK's, paladins and necros, are a substitute class that you can pick when you can't find the class you really want.  You <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> can</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do a lot of substituting, but I believe the group I originally mentioned is the best, and the more substituting you have to do, the less XP-per-minute you'll end up getting.<br>
