<br>
i have been in a group with bard, warrior, shaman, magician, rogue, rogue.  all of us had epics and close to full velious armor.  many mobs were killed very quickly that day.  there was also little to no chat, and after 2 hours it got somewhat boring.<br>
<br>
i have been in a group with magician, druid, paladin, enchanter, shadow knight, wizard.  we did not kill as many mobs as the former group.  these players, though, i all considered in game friends.  we laughed, we gossiped, we shared stories from years ago.  we made up funny emotes, we killed mobs, we had a grand ole time.  and even though we were at the same camp for the same time as the former group, i had much more fun with friends than i did killing at a mindless pace.<br>
<br>
if you want the perfect group for a magician, i would say an aoe group with-<br>
<br>
cleric<br>
enchanter<br>
enchanter<br>
magician<br>
wizard<br>
wizard<br>
<br>
with regards to effectiveness and ability to gain most xp, this group will do that for you in any zone that can hold an aoe group, and has a short respawn time (fungus grove, the grey, acrylia, howling stones are four zones that come to mind)...<br>
